title: yuka_(rhythm_tengoku)
body:
A character from the [[Rhythm Tengoku]] series, appears in every game in some form and is considered by the community the mascot of the series. Her most well-known appearance is in the stage "Tap Dance" ("Tap Trial" in English) [[dancing]] with [[monkey_(rhythm_tengoku)|monkeys]], which shows her having [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] with a [[ponytail]], and wearing a [[red dress]] with [[red footwear]]. She's also seen wearing different clothes in the series' "Remixes".

She's often called the "Tap Trial girl" by the community.

A [[girl (minna no rhythm tengoku)|very similar looking girl]], though without a proper name, also appears in the title screen for [[Minna no Rhythm Tengoku]].

title: taito
body:
[b]Taito[/b] is a legendary Japanese [[video game]] company that specializes in video games, toys, arcade cabinets, and game centers, based in Shinjuku, [[Tokyo (city)|]].

The company was founded by Ukranian entrepreneur "Michael Kogan":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Kogan in 1953 as the "Taito Trading Company", importing vodka, vending machines, and jukeboxes into [[Japan]]. It began production of video games in 1973. In 2005, Taito was purchased by [[Square Enix]], becoming a wholly-owned subsidiary by 2006.

title: paddington_bear
body:
The titular protagonist of [i][[Paddington]][/i]. Originally from Peru, he arrives as a stowaway in the [[United Kingdom]] and is so named because the Brown family, who take him in, meet him at Paddington Station in Westminster, London. Author Michael Bond based him on a lone teddy bear that he noticed on a shelf in a London shop near Paddington Station on Christmas Eve 1956, which he bought as a present for his wife.

He first appeared as a [[stuffed toy]] in 1972, manufactured by Gabrielle Designs. Shirley and Eddie Clarkson, the owners, made the prototype as a Christmas present for their children Joanna and [[Jeremy Clarkson|Jeremy]], who went on to become a car journalist and TV host ([i][[Top Gear]][/i]/[i]The Grand Tour[/i]).

Statues of him can be found at Platform 1 at Paddington, in Leicester Square in London and in Parque Salazar, Miraflores, Lima, Peru.

title: grape-kun
body:
A male [[Humboldt penguin]] who lived at "Tobu Zoo":http://www.tobuzoo.com/global/english/ in Saitama Prefecture. Grape-kun obtained Internet fame in 2017 for his interactions with a cardboard cutout of [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i]' [[humboldt_penguin_(kemono_friends)|Hululu the Humboldt Penguin]] character placed in his enclosure as part of a promotional event, prompting many to consider Grape-kun an old friend of hers, a secret admirer, or as being hopelessly in love with her while being stuck in the third dimension, the latter leading many animanga fans to sympathize with the penguin. He became a sensation, receiving many visitors and a plethora of online fanart depicting him alongside Hululu and even a visit from Hululu's anime voice actress, [[Chikuta Ikuko]].

He was distinguishable from other Humboldt penguins at the Tobu Zoo by the purple [[armband]] on his left flipper.

According to zoo staff, Grape used to have a wife called Midori (distinguished from her green flipper band, [i]midori[/i] being the Japanese word for that color), but at some point she abandoned Grape-kun and found a new lover— a rather exceptional occurrence in a species that usually forms lifelong pair bonds, and a source of suggestion as to why Grape-kun grew so attached to the Hululu cutout.

Grape-kun passed away from a sudden illness on October 12, 2017, at the age of 21. A temporary message board was set up near his enclosure for visitors to leave parting words, and many additionally left gifts such as artwork and flowers.

title: station_master_tama
body:
The Cat That Saved A Railway Line.

Tama (たま), 29 April 1999 – 22 June 2015) was a female calico cat who gained fame for being a station master and operating officer at Kishi Station on the Kishigawa Line in Kinokawa, Wakayama, Japan.

Tama was born in Kinokawa, Wakayama, and was raised with a group of stray cats that used to live close to Kishi Station. In January 2007, railway officials decided to officially name Tama the station master. As station master, her primary duty was to greet passengers. The position came with a station master's hat; in lieu of a salary, the railway provided Tama with cat food. At the time, the local railway line was almost bankrupt and the station was unmanned but Tama's celebrity status helped to bring the company back from the brink of financial ruin 

Tama died on June 22nd 2015 of apparent heart failure at the age of 16 at an animal hospital in Wakayama Prefecture. After her passing, thousands of her fans from all over Japan came to pay their respect. She was honored with a Shinto-style funeral at the station and was given the posthumous title, "honorable eternal stationmaster."

title: mikazuki_munechika
body:
A [i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i] character. Based off of the [[tachi (weapon)|tachi]] [i]Mikazuki[/i] crafted by Sanjou Munechika currently housed in the Tokyo National Museum as a national treasure. One of the "Five Swords Under Heaven", along with [[Juzumaru Tsunetsugu]] and [[Oodenta Mitsuyo]].

In-game, he appears as a [[blue_hair|blue-haired]] young man with [[blue eyes]]. He wears a black [[hairband]] with golden [[tassel]]s, [[black gloves]] and a [[hakama skirt]] underneath a [[sayagata]] patterned [[kariginu]]. The crescent moon imagery invoked in his name (三日月 = Crescent Moon) is seen in his casual wear [[bandana]] and on the sides of his standard clothing.

Tends to be characterized as an "old man" in fanworks, since he introduces himself as an old man due to being "born" near the end of the 11th century. This either manifests in a wise, ancient personality or that of a doddering old fool in comedic works. For the most part he also tends to be characterized as a rather teasing person based on a few of his lines. Knows a thing or two about [[Honebami Toushirou]]'s past, but refuses to tell him anything about it.

He shares the same name as [[mikazuki (kancolle)|Mikazuki]]  from [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i] due to the historical ship being named after the sword, and as a result is often paired with her in various [[crossover]] fanart. Their grouping is tagged "三日月爺孫":http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E4%B8%89%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%88%E7%88%BA%E5%AD%AB ("Mikazuki Grandfather-Daughter") in pixiv, as Mikazuki the sword spirit is a self-proclaimed old man (and thus the grandfather), while his ship-girl counterpart is a very young girl (hence the grand-daughter).

Because of his status as one of the hardest to obtain swords in the game, he's become rather infamous, and has appeared in multiple media as a borderline mascot for the franchise.

Voiced by Toriumi Kosuke. Character designer is [[sata (ipev)|]].

title: mount_rushmore
body: A mountain in the Black Hills near Keystone, South Dakota, in the [[United States]]. It is most well known as an American national memorial for its sculpture called the Shrine of Democracy carved into its granite face. Sculpted by Danish-American Gutzon Borglum and his son, Lincoln Borglum, it features 60-foot (18 m) sculptures of the heads of four US Presidents: [[George Washington]] (1732–1799), [[Thomas Jefferson]] (1743–1826), [[Theodore Roosevelt]] (1858–1919), and [[Abraham Lincoln]] (1809–1865). h4. External Links * "Official website (US National Park Service)":[https://www.nps.gov/moru/index.htm]

title: wriggle_nightbug
body:
The "Bug of Light Wriggling in the Dark". Stage 1 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Imperishable Night]][/i].
A youkai insect (in her case, based on a [[firefly]]) with the ability to manipulate insects. She is best known, however, for the confusion surrounding her gender (due to her [[androgynous]] appearance) prior to the full release of IN. Doujins portray her as a member of [[Team 9 (touhou)|]], a posse of low-tier Touhou characters alongside [[Cirno]], [[Mystia Lorelei]] and [[Rumia]]. Also humorously called "G" (short for "gokiburi", Japanese for "cockroach"), due to the antennae on her head. She is also frequently associated with [[Kazami Yuuka]], because they have similar hairstyles and because bugs pollinate flowers.

h4. Appearance
* !asset #23345172
She has [[short hair|short]] [[green hair]] and [[green eyes]] with thin [[antennae]] on her head. Her outfit is a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt]] with [[long sleeves]], a [[two-sided cape|two-sided]] [[black cape|black]] and [[red cape]], [[blue shorts|blue]] or [[black shorts]], [[white socks]], and either [[red footwear|red]] [[mary janes]] or [[brown footwear|brown]] [[loafers]].

Her skirt gains an [[argyle trim]] around the hem, replacing the black trim from before. Her sleeves extend [[sleeves_past_wrists|past her wrists]] stopping at the knuckles.

Her rigging retains a similar structure though the mechanical arms are given more length and mobility. Two hull segments are present on the ends of both mechanical arms, as well as two smaller hull segments near the body. She also has two [[depth_charge_projector|depth charge projectors]] near the body.

title: joy_mech_fight
body:
Japanese Title: ジョイメカファイト
Alternate Name: Joy Mech Fight

A fighting game released on the [[Famicom]]. Developed by Koichi Hayashida and Kochiro Ito, and published by [[Nintendo]] for their own system in 1993.

Robots apparently made of choreographed and independently propelled disembodied parts are pitted against each other two at a time, like in [[capcom|Capcom's]] [[Street Fighter II (series)|Street Fighter II]].

The game is notable for being a hilariously ingenious, if not completely successful, fighting game developed within the tight constraints of the Famicom's graphical capabilities. By clever design, Joy Mech Fight offered a roster of 36 fighters complete with special moves and fast-paced gameplay, well ahead of most contemporary conventional fighting games.

title: eurobeat
body:
A music style characterized by fast beats per minute, heavy synthesizers, occasional guitars, and dramatic vocals. Originally spawned off of Italo disco with a handful of Italian labels pioneering the genre; now an international cult sensation, with the majority of it's creators releasing songs primarily in Japan.

In the west the style is mainly known via [[Dance Dance Revolution]] and other rhythm games, as well as the [[Initial D]] anime and manga series; both which showcase a wide variety of artists.

Avex Trax holds the longest running anthology of eurobeat, with its Super Eurobeat (SEB) series. [[Vocaloid]], [[Touhou]], and even automobile franchises have all sprouted their very own spin of Eurobeat, eg. Toho Eurobeat (TEB).

Often compared to Pop, Electronic Dance Music, House, Dubstep, and R&B; due to the ambiguous and niche nature of the genre, it's hard to pinpoint and classify it, making it one the most versatile musical styles in the world.

The dancing style [[Para Para]] is often associated with Eurobeat.

h4. See Also:

title: yu_mei-ren_(fate)
body:
An Assassin-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[brown hair|brown]]-[[black hair]], wears a [[black dress]] and [[dual wielding|wields]] two [[sword]]s. In her unascended form she has a [[braided ponytail]] and wears [[glasses]]. In her ascended form, she removes her glasses and has unbraided hair.

Historically she was known as the lover of [[Xiang Yu (fate)|]]. In Type-Moon lore she is an immortal hermit, a species of natural spirit and a vampire similar to "True Ancestors":http://typemoon.wikia.com/wiki/True_Ancestor like [[Arcueid Brunestud]]. Since she's been ostracized by humans for millennia for being a vampire, she greatly hates mankind. She also deeply despises [[Koyanskaya (fate)|]] because she witnessed "Daji":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daji, another incarnation of the Great Fox, bring down an empire.

She has three different appearances, depending on her Ascension level:

* Stage 1: [[Pinstripe pattern|Pinstripe]] [[turtleneck]], [[glasses]], long [[braided ponytail]]. This Ascension has been given a dedicated character tag, see [b]Costumes[/b] below.
* Stage 2: Revealing [[black dress]], no glasses, unbraided hair.
* Stage 3: Like stage 2, but with a [[fur-trimmed jacket]].

[spoilers]As her unascended form indicates, she is the true identity of [[Akuta Hinako]].[/spoilers]

title: nase_fumino
body:
Supporting character from [i][[Umamusume: Cinderella Gray]][/i].  [[Super Creek (umamusume)|]]'s [[trainer (umamusume)|]] from the Cinderella Gray manga continuity.

Appears as a young woman with [[short hair|short]] to [[medium hair|medium]] hair with prominent [[swept bangs]] nearly covering her left eye.

Speculated by fans to be a genderswapped alternate universe version of famed Japanese jockey (and Umamusume commercial regular) [[Take Yutaka]] because of their similar backgrounds (ie. both Yutaka and Fumino having well-known fathers who are/were in the same business). title: kamen_rider_2
body:
The second protagonist of the original Kamen Rider television series.

After [[kamen rider 1|Takeshi Hongo]]'s desertion of Shocker, [[Ichimonji Hayato]] is kidnapped and reconstructed into a cyborg with the sole purpose of eliminating Kamen Rider, but is rescued by Hongo before brainwashing could take place.

Ichimonji is christened the second Kamen Rider and joins Hongo in his fight against Shocker.

title: kamen_rider_1
body:
One of the two protagonists of the original series that kicked off the [[Kamen Rider]] franchise.

[[hongou takeshi|Takeshi Hongo]] is kidnapped by the terrorist organization, Shocker, and surgically altered into a cyborg. Hongo, however, manages to escape before being brainwashed to do Shocker's bidding and uses his new power to begin his war against evil as the first Kamen Rider.

To avoid confusion with [[kamen rider 2|No. 2]], his gloves and boots are white. In Kamen Rider the First and the Next he is dark blue with a white belt.

title: geymalk
body:
A fictional manned giant combat [[robot]] from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in the [[Gundam ZZ]] anime TV series from 1986.

[b]AMX-015 Geymalk[/b]

A heavy assault and psycommu equipped Newtype use [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by [[Haman Karn]]'s [[Neo Zeon]]. In addition to being equiped with mega-particle guns all over its body, it possessed two "mother funnels" with 28 total bit remote weapons between them. 

This overwhelming firepower made the Geymalk perhaps the most heavily armed and dangerous suit produced by Axis during the First Neo Zeon War. While it was intended to have been mass produced, only one unit was ever built and given to [[Chara Soon]].

title: warrior_cats
body:
A long-running children's book series created by a group of authors under the pseudonym Erin Hunter. It focuses on groups of anthropomorphized feral cats that compete for resources and their political conflicts.

It is popular around the world and has been running since 2003, though is espeically popular in China, being one of the countries to quickly recieve translations of the books, as well as exclusive merchandise to the region.

The series is divided into several six-book arcs that are largely contained as their own stories within the larger narrative.

h4. Arcs

* [[The Prophecies Begin]] (2003-2004)
* [[The New Prophecy]] (2005-2006)

body:

Takes the form of a floating humanoid of baby-like proportions with a large, white onion-shaped head and a light cyan body, wearing white gloves, a yellow [[scarf]] and brown boots.
It has a pair of [[white wings]] on its back, two bright red [[blush stickers]] on its cheeks and a pair of shiny black horn-like protrusions on the sides of its head. On its forehead is a digital read-out that counts the amount of energy debt the victim targeted by it has accumulated; once the debt exceeds the victim's available aura, it transforms into [[Toritaten]].

Called A.P.R. ("Amortizing Power Redirector") in the English translation.

Voiced in the anime adaptation by [[Kaneda Tomoko]].

title: apocalypse_(eve_online)
body:
Class of a [[spacecraft|spaceship]]s in the [[EVE Online]].

«In days past, only those in high favor with the Emperor could hope to earn the reward of commanding one of the majestic and powerful Apocalypse class battleships. In latter years, even though now in full market circulation, these golden, metallic monstrosities are still feared and respected as enduring symbols of Amarrian might.»

The Apocalypse (or "Apoc") is a Tech 1 [[Amarr Empire (EVE Online)|Amarr]] [[Attack ship (EVE Online)|Attack]] [[Battleship (EVE Online)|]]. It is the ultimate entry in the Amarr line of sniping laserboats after the Tormentor, [[Coercer (EVE Online)|]], [[Omen (EVE Online)|]], and [[Harbinger (EVE Online)|]]. It has bonuses to large energy [[turret]] optimal range and tracking speed. Together with the ability of energy turrets to switch crystals instantly, these bonuses make it perform well at different engagement ranges. Pulse [[laser]] Apocalypses with Tech 2 Scorch ammunition are able to deliver good damage at a decent distance. Apocalypses are also well suited to beam laser long-range fits.

Derivative classes: 
* Apocalypse Imperial Issue ([[Special Edition ship (EVE Online)|Special Edition version]])
* Apocalypse Navy Issue ([[Imperial Navy (EVE Online)|]] modification)
* [[Paladin (EVE Online)|]] ([[Marauder (EVE Online)|]])

title: gon_freecss
body:
The main protagonist of [[Hunter x Hunter]].

Gon is an athletic, rustic, and friendly young boy who had longed dreamed of becoming a Hunter like his father, [[Ging Freecss]]. In fact, the main reason Gon joined the Hunter Exam was so he could find Ging, and to see why he valued being a Hunter more than taking care of his own son. In the Hunter Exam, Gon finds [[Kurapika]], [[leorio_paladiknight|Leorio]] and [[killua_zoldyck|Killua]], the other three main characters of the series. Killua later becomes his best friend.

h5. Visual characteristics
Gon has [[spiked_hair|spiky]] [[black_hair|black]] and [[green_hair|green]] tipped [[multicolored_hair|hair]] and [[brown eyes]]. His usual outfit is composed of a [[green jacket]] with reddish edges covering a [[black_tank_top|black]] or [[white_tank_top|white tank top]] underneath. He also wears [[green shorts]] and [[green_footwear|green]] [[boots]]. In some arcs such as the [i]Greed Island[/i] and [i]Chimera Ants[/i] he wears only the tank top.

title: killua_zoldyck
body:
One of the four main characters of [[Hunter x Hunter]].

Killua is a boy with a calm and laid back personality, however, his ruthlessness and aptitude in killing show the other side of him—deadly, violent, and bloodthirsty. He is a member of a famous family of assassins, the Zoldyck Family. He is the third son of [[Silva Zoldyck|Silva]] and [[kikyou_zoldyck|Kikyou]]. Killua is considered a promising member of the family but ends up running away from home and entering the Hunter Exam. Killua ends up meeting [[Kurapika]], [[leorio_paladiknight|Leorio]] and [[gon_freecss|Gon]], the other three main characters of the series. Gon later becomes his best friend. 

h4. Appearance

Killua is a young boy with [[white_hair|white]], [[messy_hair|messy]] [[spiked_hair|spiky hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. He typically wears a [[long_sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[blue_shirt|blue]]/[[black_shirt|black]] [[shirt]] with [[turtleneck]] under a [[white_shirt|white]] [[t-shirt]]. He also wears [[blue_shorts|blue]]/[[purple shorts]] and [[purple footwear|purple]] [[shoes]] (recolored [[brown footwear|brown]] in the 1999 adaptation). title: gu_yuena
body:
The Silver Dragon King, and heroine of Douluo Dalu 3, and 4. 

Her sealed forms from Douluo Dalu 3 are Gu Yue, and Na'er before they merged together. She is the main love interest of Tang Wulin in Douluo Dalu 3, but has to constantly reject his romantic advances due to being a part of the nearly extinct spirit beast race. By Douluo Dalu 4 their feelings are finally reciprocated.

Associated:
[[Na'er_(douluo_dalu)]]: She is the other half of their sealed power. She holds the power of the Silver Dragon Spear with the power to devour Life energy. Ultimately she forgets her memories as a spirit beast, and is content with living as a human alongside [[Tang_wulin_(douluo_dalu)]]
[[Gu_yue_(douluo_dalu)]]: She inherited the second half of the sealed power. She held the elemental power of the Silver Dragon King, and leadership of the spirit beast race. Her goal was to devour Tang Wulin to regain the power of the Golden Dragon King and ascend back into the Dragon God to destroy humanity. However, she loses the will to fulfill her plan after she fell in love with Tang Wulin.

title: jojifuku
body:
Adults wearing nostalgic children's clothing such as [[kindergarten uniform]]s, [[randoseru]], and brands such as [[Mezzo Piano]]. Considered to be a subcategory of the [[heisei retro]] style.

Derived from the hashtag "大人なのに女児服着てる" (otonananoni jojifuku ki teru) - "even though I'm an adult, I'm wearing girls' clothes".

This term is sometimes also used to refer to the heisei retro style in general - this tag is specifically for adults wearing children's clothing, however, and should not be used on pictures of children.
